            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650971037604-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>orange</strong> to a bowl along with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>,<strong> remaining soy sauce </strong>and <strong>remaining cornflour</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and mix until fully combined – this is your<strong> orange sauce</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, peel and slice the <strong>remaining orange</strong> into triangles</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650971040868-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650971040868-x400.jpg",
